<br>
<br>
I know other classes you listed have much different roles then listed as well.<br>
<br>
The trial for bards would ignore a great majority of what they can accomplish, druids actually have nukes and dot's, mages arent just 'fido - kill', the monk one sounds absurdly easy, and putting a time limit on anything that involves 'avoiding ht mobs' doesnt sound like fun (i have some experience pulling giants and stuff).  There is no manadump component in the necro trial <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , Rangers arent all 'melee melee plink plink plink', they are, above and beyond, the best outdoors pullers. Shadowknights do more then melee and tap stuff. Shaman... buffs. shaman... buffs. You either never group with good shaman, or you never group with shaman.  Wizards arent just rootbomb/rootnuke/kamikaziedeathmanaburn.<br>
