Im sure theres more. <p><div align=center> <a target=“new” href = http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=429465> Sir Barraind Faylestar, Lord Protector </a><br><br><blockquote><font color=00ccff>What do you get when you take a warm heart, soothing hand, a trusting shoulder, ears meant to listen, add to them  an impish smirk, eyes of truth, and a playfull nature? Nothing. If you added it to a loyal spirit, an everloving soul, and the drive to always do what is right, you get a paladin. But something is missing... always missing... thats what we fight for. </font><br> <font color = cc0000><cite>If its not worth fighting for, give it up. If its not worth dying for, give it up. If its worth that and more, keep fighting. One day, you might not have to. Never trust a man on the merit of what he once was or will be. Only trust what he is.</cite></font></blockquote><br><font color=cc0000>I am Lord Protector, paladin d00d, that guy, insane, troubled, whatever you want to call me of</font> <a target =“new” href= http://www.evguild.org> The Elitists and Vagrants</a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sasner123>Sasner123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/8/02 3:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2320.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trails</span><hr size=1> like I said I'm sure I missed a bunch of things for each class, grant my exp is limited to my character, I just think it would be an interesting way to separate the men from the boys so to speak.  what I listed off were just ideas I came up with after being up way too late and having prob to much coffee as well.  I just really think it would be interesting