<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=346700">Sasner's Magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=camthan>camthan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Cleric of Love</span><br>  Posts: 415<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/8/02 5:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2320.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trails</span><hr size=1> While I think if they could make a trial to truly test someones skill, that would be great. However, SoE would never do it because- most of the roles we are 'assigned' automatically just aren't what they intended them to be. <br>
<br>
Everquest was not designed for people to sit in one place and pull mobs. It was designed for the entire group to keep on moving. Monks FD was not meant as a pulling tool, which is why it is nerfed now, and mobs over level 45 do not have a 100% chance of losing all agro. It was meant as a defensive measure because monks generate a lot of agro. Besides bad coding, I think SoE adds bad pathing in some places so monks can't/have a very hard time pulling. Shaman and druids were not (at first) intended to heal anywhere past level 39 or so. The reason they were given heals was, from a role play perspective, shaman were not always from a race that would group with other races. IE Ogres and trolls would never group with a cleric, except maybe a dark elf. Barbarians were way out in the middle of nowhere, so they needed healers out there for a while. Necro and druid roles have changed dramatically since release, as have most other classes. Hell, as a cleric I'm not even sure I should heal anymore <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
