<br>
Having &quot;simulated&quot; groups would be an idea (IE an NPC cleric in the group who is programmed to complete heal whenever someone is 40 percent life) but that doesnt allow for thinking on the fly and communication which are both sooo important in groups.  I don't care if you're a monk and can successfully single pull a mob through a group of 20 casters to your group...if you're a warrior who can solo a red con...a chanter who is able to mezz 15 mobs without getting a scratch...I am more impressed by groups that function well together and work as a team to do something that seems impossible.<br>
<br>
Plus, you're trying to get flagged for a special place where you're going to group the whole time...so why should you have to do something on your own to get in?<br>
