<br>
Every class has their own advantages, and disadvantages.  Most are extremely versatile and lend themselves to multiple play styles.  Based partly on abilities.  And partly on gear.  Trying to play balance that would just be a massive time sink.<br>
<br>
The term &quot;trial&quot; brings to mind pitting each class, not against things where their abilities often excel.  But instead where they are weakest.  I'd definitely find more of a challenge, and fun, in overcoming my handicap, than doing the same thing I do every day.<br>
<br>
Having played both Thief, and Thief 2, I can say spending an hour waiting and watchig mob pathing to sneak through a trial would be rather boring.  Especially knowing that even a level 1 rogue could do it.  Afterwhich, Paralyze 3 and Intimidation would make the DPS encounter simply silly.  With root nets, you can keep at it till the mob was dead with little harm or danger since you have plenty of time to re-apply poisons.<br>
<br>
The main reason Verrant didn't do singular trials simply follows their plan.  Teamwork.  It's always been about teamwork.  And it always will.<br>
